.Os
.Dt VFS_UNMOUNT 9
.Sh NAME
.Nm VFS_UNMOUNT
.Nd unmount a filesystem
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In sys/param.h
.In sys/mount.h
.In sys/vnode.h
.Ft int
.Fn VFS_UNMOUNT "struct mount *mp" "int mntflags" "struct proc *p"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
Unmount a filesystem.
.Pp
Its arguments are:
.Bl -tag -width mntflags
.It Ar mp
The filesystem.
.It Ar mntflags
Various flags.
.It Ar p
Process which is unmounting the filesystem.
.El
.Pp
If the
.Dv MNT_FORCE
flag is specified then open files should be forcibly closed.
